 higher likelihood. We illustrate that the\nrejection of non-desired and re-selection of preferred vaccines fragments the\npopulation by the mRNA versus other type of vaccines while it generally\nimproves the assessment of the received vaccine. These results highlight that\ngreater variance of available vaccine types and individual free choice are\ndesirable conditions that can widen the acceptance of vaccines in societies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 11 Nov 2021 21:05:02 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 4 Jan 2022 10:38:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-01-05"}
