cted in many SR-CPM simulation practices. We proposed\nthat the optimised $\\alpha_i$ or $U_i^0$ should compensate for the electrical\npotential/energy discrepancy between the discrete atomistic model and the\ncontinuum limit. The analytical and optimal ${\\alpha}_i^0$ values are derived\nfor a series of 2D materials.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 12 Nov 2021 13:06:21 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 3 May 2022 02:37:24 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-05-04"}
